This paper deals with algorithmic solutions to the problem of manipulating sequential allocation, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the development of novel algorithms, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.THE). The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
